1
00:00:05,225 --> 00:00:09,005
These descriptions are 
divinely descended

2
00:00:09,275 --> 00:00:11,207
from the upper world,

3
00:00:11,816 --> 00:00:13,949
so we have to revere
not only their content,

4
00:00:13,949 --> 00:00:16,622
but their structure,
many things,

5
00:00:17,177 --> 00:00:21,352
and offer ourselves
in service to them.

6
00:00:21,613 --> 00:00:24,645
[Offering Oneself to the Truth]

7
00:00:25,009 --> 00:00:26,940
It’s all about service.

8
00:00:26,940 --> 00:00:29,995
Guru Mahārāj quotes
Professor Sanyal,

9
00:00:29,995 --> 00:00:34,111
revealing to him early on
in the days of Gauḍīya Math,

10
00:00:34,111 --> 00:00:37,044
“If I go to read the Bhāgavatam

11
00:00:37,629 --> 00:00:40,197
under the guidance 
of Guru and Vaiṣṇava,

12
00:00:40,197 --> 00:00:43,456
on their order,
it may be devotion.

13
00:00:43,995 --> 00:00:50,808
If I go on my own, it may be karma,
it may be vikarma.”

14
00:00:50,808 --> 00:00:55,163
Same story, same words,
everything’s there.

15
00:00:55,163 --> 00:00:58,538
One’s a devotional act,
another one could be karma

16
00:00:58,538 --> 00:01:00,720
or vikarma, even detrimental.

17
00:01:02,641 --> 00:01:06,360
What is activating 
the spiritual current

18
00:01:06,360 --> 00:01:08,383
is the order of the Vaiṣṇava,

19
00:01:08,383 --> 00:01:13,258
in pursuance of the order 
of the Vaiṣṇava.

20
00:01:13,258 --> 00:01:16,565
Pursuit of serving the order
of the Vaiṣṇava.

21
00:01:17,395 --> 00:01:20,170
“Ādau arpita paśchat kriyeta.”

22
00:01:20,170 --> 00:01:21,900
Beginning, middle and end.

23
00:01:21,900 --> 00:01:25,693
If, really, this is being done
as an offering,

24
00:01:26,553 --> 00:01:30,620
and one is offering oneself
in service,

25
00:01:31,881 --> 00:01:35,297
as Kavirāj Goswāmī says,
Sanātan Goswāmī says,

26
00:01:35,297 --> 00:01:39,146
“It is not I who am writing
Chaitanya-charitāmṛta,

27
00:01:39,146 --> 00:01:41,677
but some divine power 
has descended

28
00:01:41,677 --> 00:01:43,777
and is moving my hand

29
00:01:43,777 --> 00:01:46,561
and making me write or 
express these things.

30
00:01:46,837 --> 00:01:49,723
It is Madan Mohan’s work.”

31
00:01:50,735 --> 00:01:52,738
He’s speaking like that.

32
00:01:54,455 --> 00:01:56,477
What did Saraswatī Ṭhākur say

33
00:01:56,477 --> 00:01:58,947
about Bhakti Vinod 
Viraha Dasakam?

34
00:01:58,947 --> 00:02:02,712
Bhakti Vinod Ṭhākur
has written this through him,

35
00:02:04,142 --> 00:02:05,880
it’s that perfect.

36
00:02:06,527 --> 00:02:08,659
It’s as if Bhakti Vinod Ṭhākur 
has written this

37
00:02:08,659 --> 00:02:11,112
through him, through his pen.

38
00:02:12,501 --> 00:02:14,343
That’s for writing, 
but it’s also

39
00:02:14,343 --> 00:02:17,135
for perceiving, receiving, 
all of these things.

